<subSubSection id="7B70A240EBF4A3F935F09F0448C56892" pageId="127" pageNumber="128" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="93E45C82A28C8BF095F8872A27CB6E87" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">
102b. 
<taxonomicName id="AD675EDBB8FA96F65D6885E12C5E3181" LSID="F5A9D5DC-C72E-5398-8DAF-A05D4E638E95" authority="R. R. Mill ex J. R. I. Wood &amp; R. W. Scotland" authorityName="R. R. Mill ex J. R. I. Wood &amp; R. W. Scotland" authorityYear="2015" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus glomeratus subsp. var. var. sachalitarum" order="Solanales" pageId="127" pageNumber="128" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="glomeratus" status="var. nov." subSpecies="var." variety="sachalitarum">Convolvulus glomeratus var. sachalitarum R.R.Mill ex J.R.I.Wood &amp; R.W.Scotland</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="800E005B66AC1D1BE43768BE4F8EAB89" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">var. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B9833830875C7DEDCB016957DF8C54F5" pageId="127" pageNumber="128" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="C5E2A9C3E93FDAFE28281181B0EA1483" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AECDCEC90DECF1BE802030D780A5476E" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">A subsp. typo corolla 15-20 mm longa (non &lt;12 mm longa) et usque 2.5 cm diametro dignoscenda.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9B3612ED98673FE6A656398E4FFFFCC8" pageId="127" pageNumber="128" type="type">
<paragraph id="D8AE369301FA0DFFBF7988D3EF3D510C" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">Type.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="186A0881A1620DF102CB1D8928DFE1F0" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">
OMAN, Dhofar, Cliff near Dalkut, 
<emphasis id="BAB98034AB437554CE5059DB6286A5EC" italics="true" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">McLeish</emphasis>
2813 (holotype E00132890!).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E7CAF1EEF134DCBB89DCCF3E4AE3A839" pageId="127" pageNumber="128" type="distinguishing features">
<paragraph id="61006CC8CAD9764685709FD2F64FC737" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">Distinguishing features.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6A4E5254C2D55F0A7751B3509DF0987A" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">
The key feature of this variety is the very large corolla 1.5-2 cm long when dry and up to 2.5 cm in diameter when living. The leaves are always relatively large, up to 4 
<normalizedToken id="CB7CEE1DA2C5BE346D4A4488B898C329" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2.5 cm, the peduncles long and commonly gently curved, reaching 7 cm in length, and the sepals may reach 12 mm. However, all characters apart from the corolla size can be matched in other populations of 
<taxonomicName id="CB63A62C5E0AB65498D5F2C9BE9BF523" authorityName="Hochst. ex Choisy, Prodr. [A. P. de Candolle] 9: 401. 1845. (Choisy" authorityYear="1845" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus glomeratus" order="Solanales" pageId="127" pageNumber="128" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="glomeratus">
<emphasis id="E733DE8B578DE8447ED6D8EA0F9502FC" italics="true" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">Convolvulus glomeratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and as the corolla size is hardly constant, varietal status seems appropriate.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="74979391839042C1EFC3BCF9BCCED5CD" pageId="127" pageNumber="128" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="52D09B97E5C31113DD78BB7F73BB24FD" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="98A929BD32AB55F80EF61F38EF6AA421" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">
Oman (Dhofar): 
<emphasis id="FC4C5574944D362BDCD866A89AA92132" italics="true" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">McLeish</emphasis>
697, 2248, 2415, 2661, 2814; 
<emphasis id="664623A92841FCEF9A77A34E82C1773D" italics="true" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">Ash</emphasis>
126; 
<emphasis id="4B44478BF29FCB5D9C7C0FF09CB17765" italics="true" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">Collenette</emphasis>
8347; 
<emphasis id="A03B46470C98ACB7620B0CD00C30058E" italics="true" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">Miller</emphasis>
2262, 2331, 2356; 
<emphasis id="2B5A344D4373D256181956D3EB547ADB" italics="true" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">Miller &amp; Whitcombe</emphasis>
2082.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="1092C9E57303B3064EB60A224BFAAD98" pageId="127" pageNumber="128" type="notes">
<paragraph id="DC8CBC1C84C6AAF52065E3D56E64B31F" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FD501E4E233B82843BCD41A672958DDD" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">
There has been some uncertainty about the correct name for this species. 
<taxonomicName id="87B4210BBAE9DE625EB940549C619D50" authorityName="Hochst. ex Choisy, Prodr. [A. P. de Candolle] 9: 401. 1845. (Choisy" authorityYear="1845" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus glomeratus" order="Solanales" pageId="127" pageNumber="128" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="glomeratus">
<emphasis id="8C100FE5DF2CF39D385F91C71C667E90" italics="true" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">Convolvulus glomeratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Thunb. is a 
<emphasis id="1C6996FC6FDE9EC99E545781085B308B" italics="true" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">nomen nudum</emphasis>
so the combination 
<taxonomicName id="51E445ABB51EB90C78FCB931CECA7E16" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus auricomus" order="Solanales" pageId="127" pageNumber="128" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="auricomus">
<emphasis id="6FBB19A03EFC23A63C42720AB1989EB9" italics="true" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">Convolvulus auricomus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is unnecessary. 
<taxonomicName id="C445B1F8C5B6961013A76725CF5C5550" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus arabicus" order="Solanales" pageId="127" pageNumber="128" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="arabicus">
<emphasis id="AD80BCF62D76B5D106AA52617C6378BE" italics="true" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">Convolvulus arabicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Hochst. &amp; Steud. also appears to be a 
<emphasis id="78963D30740B4E5789F9E217F30480A0" italics="true" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">nomen nudum</emphasis>
, so 
<taxonomicName id="3EF931D9BB694230128213277566EC9C" authorityName="Hochst. ex Choisy, Prodr. [A. P. de Candolle] 9: 401. 1845. (Choisy" authorityYear="1845" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus glomeratus" order="Solanales" pageId="127" pageNumber="128" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="glomeratus">
<emphasis id="A77C37160466031E8CD7945DDCB05AC6" italics="true" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">Convolvulus glomeratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
remains the accepted name. 
<taxonomicName id="2957B986C2A81CEAB968775D0C9F395A" authorityName="Parsa" authorityYear="1948" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus zargarianus" order="Solanales" pageId="127" pageNumber="128" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="zargarianus">
<emphasis id="9439FEFE2F79121408F0EE1AB48B2E90" italics="true" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">Convolvulus zargarianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="0E75F9A04FCF1417CDBDB14868A7E7DD" authorityName="Hochst. ex Choisy, Prodr. [A. P. de Candolle] 9: 401. 1845. (Choisy" authorityYear="1845" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus glomeratus" order="Solanales" pageId="127" pageNumber="128" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="glomeratus">
<emphasis id="AFF2B51BE72CE5495B11234197F616C1" italics="true" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">Convolvulus glomeratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Although 
<normalizedToken id="A07770B7B03141D7F6B20B197CF96B57" originalValue="Sa’ad">Sa'ad</normalizedToken>
describes the ovary as velutinous and the style as hairy and shows this in her illustration, this is an error.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
